<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-09-05T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-09-05T14:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1139: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at
                                Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Blake</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-09-05T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September 5,
                                        1925—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>9. In order to remove any misapprehensions which may have been caused by
                            the reported enlistments of American citizens in the Sultan’s Army, it
                            is suggested that you may consider the advisability of taking measures
                            to invite the attention of American citizens in Morocco to the
                            provisions of Sections 5282 and 4090, Revised Statutes of the United
                            States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
